Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.86,0:00:10.11,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Stop trying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.82,0:00:13.07,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,to put on a tough front around your friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.48,0:00:15.07,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Natsuki Subaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.57,0:00:18.06,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Your head is just a big, jumbled mess,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.06,0:00:20.24,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,and you don't know what to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.85,0:00:23.54,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You keep getting into situations where \Nyou have to reach out and help,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.54,0:00:26.23,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,but both your arms and your head \Nare too weak to reach far enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.23,0:00:29.88,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,so you end up just wasting time \Nfrantically flailing around, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.94,0:00:33.51,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.06,0:00:36.72,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,If you hear me, say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.35,0:00:38.55,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What the hell was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.69,0:00:43.12,Default,OttO,0,0,0,,You finally lost your temper,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.12,0:00:45.33,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,but you forgot to pay \Nattention to your footing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.33,0:00:48.60,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,That just sums you up perfectly, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.60,0:00:49.54,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.54,0:00:51.63,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Oh, is that right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.91,0:00:59.66,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,That's really all the strength you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.59,0:01:04.12,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Putting on a tough act for \Na girl you love is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.50,0:01:07.61,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,And you can play tough for \Na girl who likes you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.61,0:01:08.83,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,No one would object to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.39,0:01:11.80,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,But that's as far as it goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.61,0:01:14.80,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You know you're not good enough, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.80,0:01:16.68,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You know you can't reach, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.08,0:01:19.55,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You want to look good for the \Ngirl you like, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.55,0:01:23.00,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You want to be someone the girl who \Nlikes you can be proud of, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.76,0:01:27.10,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Then why don't you just \Naccept someone's help?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.76,0:01:28.94,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Someone like...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.53,0:01:30.77,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.25,0:01:38.07,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I did rely on someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.07,0:01:39.84,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I asked for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.63,0:01:42.27,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But it didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.92,0:01:44.62,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.44,0:01:49.83,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,But I don't recall ever \Nhearing you ask for {\i1}my{\i0} help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.08,0:01:51.92,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,N-No, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:00.49,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,My head is just full of knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.13,0:02:04.16,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,It's full of stuff you wouldn't \Nbelieve even if I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.63,0:02:06.98,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I don't even know how to start...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.68,0:02:10.69,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Just start talking. \NI'll listen until you finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:13.32,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But if I do that—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:16.43,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Didn't I just tell you not \Nto put on that tough act?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.43,0:02:19.33,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,If you have time to overcomplicate \Neverything in your head,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.33,0:02:20.82,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,then just spit it all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:22.55,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Easy for you to say, but I—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.55,0:02:24.68,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Spit out all of those knots!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.68,0:02:28.22,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,And when you're done, \Njust tell me to believe you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.22,0:02:29.85,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Because we're friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:39.55,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,You might not believe me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.63,0:02:53.65,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Roswaal!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:02:59.81,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Let's make a bet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.81,0:03:02.99,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,with my wish and yours on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:13.83,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,I certainly did not expect to \Nsee you again in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.43,0:03:17.23,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,This will be our last showdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.62,0:03:20.50,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I'm going to save the Sanctuary \Nand the mansion in this loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.50,0:03:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.44,0:03:25.50,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,And I'll bust up every \Ndamn one of your plans!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:29.01,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,You think you can start \Nover, from this dead end,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.01,0:03:33.74,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,and leave behind the one \Nand only power you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:38.28,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Being able to start over and being able \Nto save them are two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:41.78,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Both you and I were too arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.27,0:03:45.54,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,This power I have isn't even that useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.77,0:03:48.64,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,If you say this is the last time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.11,0:03:51.73,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,what is it you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.73,0:03:53.50,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,My demand is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.16,0:03:57.84,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,If I save both the Sanctuary \Nand the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.29,0:04:00.95,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,you will throw that book \Naway and come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:02.93,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I'm going to make Emilia the new ruler,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:06.18,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,And to do that , I will need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.79,0:04:08.64,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.09,0:04:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That suggestion is absolutely warped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.87,0:04:13.23,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Do you think you would \Nforgive what I—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:15.85,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,If this was about forgiving you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.85,0:04:18.25,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,there's no way in hell I'd ever do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.62,0:04:21.03,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But that's for my own heart to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:25.86,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Nothing deadly has happened yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.86,0:04:28.20,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,So if I can solve this... you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.73,0:04:31.41,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,How can an idea be so convenient?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.78,0:04:35.05,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Hey, I love convenient ideas!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.05,0:04:37.62,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia's gonna do her best \Nto become the next ruler,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.62,0:04:40.16,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I'll be by her side to congratulate her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.16,0:04:43.01,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,And you'll be one of the\N people surrounding her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.86,0:04:45.72,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Just so you know, you're mandatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:51.32,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,You expect to fulfill your desire \Nwithout letting go of anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.32,0:04:54.29,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Not only that, but you say \Nmy involvement is necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:56.81,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,and insist on including me in \Nthe foundation for the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.66,0:04:59.65,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Do you understand Subaru-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:01.11,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:06.57,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Amount of sheer {\i1}greed{\i0} your answer has.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.28,0:05:17.72,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Your enemy has become the \Nstrongest card in play.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.72,0:05:19.83,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,That's still not enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:26.25,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,No matter how hard you fight it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot break through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:31.73,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,With Emilia-sama unable to stand, \Nthe barrier will remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:34.17,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,The Sanctuary will be covered in snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.17,0:05:36.39,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,and the mansion will sink \Ninto a bloody tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:39.77,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Yeah. Should make the sight \Nof you crying all the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:44.72,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,I see. You are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.72,0:05:48.11,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,It isn't a bad idea to lay some \Ngroundwork for the next me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.52,0:05:52.33,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,So can I take that to mean \Nyou agree to the bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:05:59.26,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Well, If that's settled,\N then let's get it started.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.10,0:06:01.13,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Subaru-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:06.42,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,The snow in the Sanctuary and the attack \Non the mansion begin in three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.34,Default,Roswaal,0,0,0,,Do try your hardest to fight it...\N and fail miserably.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:10.80,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Say what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:19.52,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Roswaal, put the clown makeup back on, \N You're throwing me off my stride.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:22.48,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,As two clowns at the mercy of fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.85,0:06:25.48,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,let's fight this out fair and square.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:33.91,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,How is the scheming \Nwith you're with your friend going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.36,0:06:35.45,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you accept what Roswaal's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:42.29,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,There's only one thing \NI value above all else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.81,0:06:45.83,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,There's no way that will ever change. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.27,0:06:49.42,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,So stop hoping that \NI will change my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:51.21,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Never say never.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.21,0:06:52.72,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Watch your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:56.78,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Are you placing your hopes in Emilia-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.12,0:07:00.10,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Yes, I am, and I believe in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.77,0:07:04.11,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama hasn't figured out \Nwhy she's been struggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.21,0:07:07.60,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Until she does, the same thing \Nwill just keep happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.91,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,We've already strayed from \Nwhat's written in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:12.95,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Roswaal is free now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.82,0:07:17.89,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,She gave me a honest advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.89,0:07:19.73,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,If wonder If she likes me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.73,0:07:21.96,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,You're still talking like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.54,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,If she heard that, she'd be furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.16,0:07:28.13,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Since Ram-san is working with the margrave,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:30.14,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,doesn't that make you enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:31.38,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Ram is an enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:39.24,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Well, now I can see how \Ndeeply you trust Ram-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.24,0:07:41.96,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,And? What happened with \Nthe margrave himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.96,0:07:43.31,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Everything's set.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:45.86,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,The bet is officially on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:47.39,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,That is good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:51.50,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Well, the margrave didn't seem to \Nhave ever lost at anything before,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.50,0:07:53.32,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,so I knew he would agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.01,0:07:56.03,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,And next is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:07:59.34,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Garfiel, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:05.71,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But first, can I just check into one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.94,0:08:10.46,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll do my part \Nof the plan as discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:12.97,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,And, as for Emilia-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:17.11,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,That's one thing where \NI can't rely on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.53,0:08:20.62,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Or should I say I can't \Nrely on myself either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.42,0:08:25.90,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I haven't even scratched the \Nsurface of what's hurting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.20,0:08:28.98,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I guess I was just scared, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.98,0:08:30.74,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.74,0:08:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to play innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:34.05,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Hey, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.05,0:08:37.78,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,So are you prepared to scratch the \Nsurface of what's hurting her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.27,0:08:41.25,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Well, I'm prepared to ask her if I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:44.93,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Unlike with Garfiel, \NI don't have to worry about dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.93,0:08:47.63,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if I should \Nlaugh at that or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:51.26,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Then again, you took a bet \Nthat was stacked against you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.68,0:08:52.99,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.45,0:08:56.47,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,But taking on a bet without even \Nconsidering my odds of winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:08:58.81,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,That's a first for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.97,0:09:10.00,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I thought I'd find you here, Ryuzu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:15.38,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,You talk like someone who already \Nknows me remarkably well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:19.16,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I'd say you're right. I know \Njust about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:21.51,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I even know what your goal is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:27.01,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Then I suppose the one Young Ros\N was waiting for was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.01,0:09:29.97,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Yeah, sorry. That whole \Nthing's been called off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.97,0:09:30.50,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Hah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:34.96,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm in the middle of a \Nhuge face-off with Roswaal now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.96,0:09:37.65,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I want it to end in a result \Nthat's good for everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.65,0:09:41.09,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,which is why I want your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.83,0:09:45.52,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Why not use your {\i1}jurisdiction{\i0} as an \Napostle to demand my assistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:47.94,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I don't want to rely on \Nthat kind of {\i1}jurisdiction{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.99,0:09:51.48,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I came here to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.49,0:09:56.49,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Young men are so quick \Nto put on a tough front.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.04,0:09:59.56,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,And? What is it you are arguing over?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:04.70,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,In simple terms, I guess I'd say \Na way to liberate the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.44,0:10:09.44,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I know you're opposed to \Nliberating it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.26,0:10:12.92,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I am opposed to liberating the Sanctuary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.28,0:10:16.31,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Huh? Wait, you're not opposed to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.78,0:10:21.05,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Haeh?! Are you for real? \NThen why did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.05,0:10:27.55,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Still, I cannot say that your \Nsuspicions are entirely wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.24,0:10:31.34,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,What is your opinion of Young Gar?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.72,0:10:36.15,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I think... there's no \Navoiding a clash with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.42,0:10:39.42,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:40.36,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.84,0:10:45.58,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,whether we can get along or not \Nafter all this is over, is yet to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.18,0:10:50.03,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,And to help me make that decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.42,0:10:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know more about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.78,0:10:59.72,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,You are quite skilled at deceiving \Nthe elderly, Young Su.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:06.89,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,You asked the witch about me, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.78,0:11:11.25,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,About the copies of Ryuzu Meyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.25,0:11:14.61,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,and perhaps about the \Npurpose of creating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.90,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I heard about the immortality experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.90,0:11:19.55,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,and that you Ryuzus were\Nthe successful cases for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.43,0:11:25.75,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,To this day, I protect and supervise \Nthe crystal that creates the copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.75,0:11:31.12,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,The four of us alternate in \Nbearing the role of supervisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:34.22,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I did hear about the "first four."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:37.08,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,So the other three besides you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:43.41,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,My name is Natsuki Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.41,0:11:45.58,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What's your name, Ryuzu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.80,0:11:49.30,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,My name is Ryuzu Arma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.30,0:11:52.64,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I am one of the first four copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.31,0:11:54.35,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Arma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.35,0:11:56.27,Default - flashback,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I am Ryuzu Bilma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:12:00.79,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,The first Ryuzu-san I met \Ncalled herself "Bilma."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:04.49,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I never meant to hide \Nanything from Ryuzu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:07.63,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But why go through so much hassle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:11.65,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Our bodies are not made of flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:15.01,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,They are made of artificial \Nod clothed in mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:18.00,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,All activity we engage in consumes the mana,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:21.21,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,and continuous activity for \Na full day is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:24.24,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Oh, so you're like the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.24,0:12:26.91,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,That's why you've been alternating \Nbetween each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:29.92,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But... are you okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:32.91,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,You are so kind, Young Su.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:41.78,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,However, one of the first four, \NRyuzu Shima, is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:43.99,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Ryuzu Shima?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.58,0:12:46.05,Default - flashback,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I will tell no one what you told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:48.91,Default - flashback,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I swear it on the name of Ryuzu Shima.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.78,0:12:53.12,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,About ten years ago, she caused a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.50,0:12:56.22,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,She was then removed from \Nthe role of supervisor,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.22,0:12:59.58,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,and now lives in the forest \Nwith the other copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.05,0:13:04.73,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,For that reason, three of us \Nfulfill the supervisor role now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.08,0:13:06.64,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What problem did she cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.14,0:13:10.28,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,She violated the contract with \Nthe witch who created us
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.28,0:13:11.84,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,by entering the graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:14.03,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,to bring back Young Gar
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when he broke the rules to attempt \Nthe trial and did not return.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.30,0:13:24.31,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I have not seen Shima since \Nshe was stripped of her duty,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.85,0:13:26.81,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,but it would be no surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.81,0:13:31.76,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,if Young Gar has been meeting with Shima, \Nwith whom he shares memories that we do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:34.01,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Memories that you three don't have?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.48,0:13:39.04,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I refer to the past that Young Gar\N saw in the graveyard trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:43.67,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Are you aware of Young Gar's family situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:48.73,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know Frederica is his \Nsister from a different father,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.73,0:13:50.49,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,and since she has less non-human blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.49,0:13:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,she left the Sanctuary ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:57.39,Default - flashback,Subaru,0,0,0,,Why did you leave the Sanctuary?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.93,0:14:02.17,Default - flashback,Frederica,0,0,0,,I suppose I wanted to create
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.70,0:14:06.58,Default - flashback,Frederica,0,0,0,,an opportunity for the \Npeople of the Sanctuary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.58,0:14:08.86,Default - flashback,Frederica,0,0,0,,to leave it once the barrier was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.65,0:14:12.16,Default - flashback,Frederica,0,0,0,,I wanted to make a place for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.89,0:14:14.74,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,At least, that's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:19.81,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Wait, did the past that Garfiel \Nsaw involve the time she left?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:22.71,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,No, what he saw was most likely
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.18,0:14:27.06,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,the moment when Young Gar \Nand Fred were left behind
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.06,0:14:29.43,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,by their mother when she left the Sanctuary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.98,0:14:33.32,Default - flashback,Echidna,0,0,0,,That foolish, pitiful Garfiel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.32,0:14:35.31,Default - flashback,Echidna,0,0,0,,fears the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:39.68,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,So the reason he's against \Nliberating the Sanctuary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.03,0:14:45.03,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,is out of bitterness toward his mother for \Nabandoning him and choosing the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.04,0:14:51.43,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,The boy refers to himself as Garfiel Tinzel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.43,0:14:53.92,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,That is his mother's family name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:58.04,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,I believe he goes by that name \Nso that he won't forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:02.97,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Whether it was out of anger or sadness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.33,0:15:08.30,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,is most likely known only to him and Shima.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.08,0:15:15.28,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia-tan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:17.11,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.47,0:15:20.35,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.20,0:15:22.90,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What're you doing down there, Emilia-tan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.90,0:15:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get your butt dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.46,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Um... I'm a restless sleeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.43,0:15:30.02,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Sorry... I lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.02,0:15:32.60,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,The truth is, I couldn't get to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.15,0:15:38.20,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,But don't worry. I'll be sure to \Nget plenty of sleep by tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.11,0:15:40.90,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,It's almost noon, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.90,0:15:43.43,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,You're talking about \Nsleeping until nightfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:46.40,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,That's very slothful of you, Emilia-tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.98,0:15:48.30,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,The way you said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.00,0:15:51.16,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,just gives me a really weird feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:53.55,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Ugh, Subaru, you meanie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.54,0:15:56.30,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.20,0:16:06.53,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia, do you feel up to telling \Nme what you saw during the trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:11.74,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I won't claim that talking about \Nit will make you feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.29,0:16:15.12,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,But if you tell me, we can \Ncarry that burden together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:17.83,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I don't know if I can be of any help...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:21.04,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,but would you give me the right to \Nfight the same enemies you fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.78,0:16:27.67,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Subaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.16,0:16:31.38,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Subaru, you have so much faith in me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.07,0:16:41.31,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.04,0:16:43.98,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,The past I saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:48.30,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,was a memory from before \NI went to sleep, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.14,0:16:55.00,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I never told you that I was frozen \Nin ice for a long time, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.00,0:16:57.27,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Frozen in... ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.27,0:17:00.66,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I was frozen in the forest for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:03.47,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Until Puck found me and got me out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.47,0:17:09.63,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I had been sleeping within the \Nice for a {\i1}long, long{\i0} time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.80,0:17:11.81,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,How long?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:15.01,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Since I was... six or \Nseven years old, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:18.07,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,We all lived in the forest together \Nbefore it froze, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.07,0:17:18.98,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.98,0:17:22.31,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I don't remember much from \Nbefore that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.79,0:17:24.42,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What about your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.88,0:17:28.02,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,My family wasn't in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.54,0:17:31.35,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,But there was someone who \Nwas like a mother to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.68,0:17:33.41,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.21,0:17:35.75,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Eh, why...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.14,0:17:38.74,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Mo.. ther?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.35,0:17:44.69,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Calm down. Take it slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.15,0:17:48.37,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What happened to all of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:51.76,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,The same... as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:53.59,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,They were frozen in ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.18,0:17:55.88,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I lived in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.06,0:18:01.05,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,always waiting with Puck\N for everyone to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.78,0:18:03.72,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,But that day never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:07.39,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,That's why... I left the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.01,0:18:09.77,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,and joined in the royal selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.77,0:18:10.30,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.79,0:18:13.65,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,What does the forest have to \Ndo with the royal selection?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.09,0:18:16.97,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Roswaal made me a promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.13,0:18:21.10,Default - flashback,Roswaal,0,0,0,,If you succeed in taking the throne,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.10,0:18:24.55,Default - flashback,Roswaal,0,0,0,,perhaps I can thaw the ice \Nthat encases this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:27.39,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Do you despise me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.10,0:18:35.21,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,All the other candidates are participating \Nwith admirable goals and resolutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:38.59,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,but my reason is {\i1}so, soo{\i0} selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.14,0:18:42.93,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Is that the "selfish reason" \Nyou were talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.98,0:18:49.26,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,There's nothing bad about wanting \Nto save the people you care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:54.15,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Even if you don't save many people,\N It's still an admirable deed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.37,0:18:56.04,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.98,0:18:59.36,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Thank you... {\i1}soo{\i0} much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.41,0:19:04.42,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.72,0:19:15.46,Default - italics,Subaru,0,0,0,,Do the memories that Emilia can't recall
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.46,0:19:18.08,Default - italics,Subaru,0,0,0,,hold some clue to getting through the trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.04,0:19:23.26,Default - italics,Subaru,0,0,0,,Maybe Emilia can't remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.56,0:19:25.22,Default - italics,,0,0,0,,but if I ask the guy who does...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:39.40,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Emilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:43.63,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.22,0:19:46.79,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,You didn't have to go that far, did you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:49.28,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Oh, I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:51.70,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Your love seems like the needy type,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.70,0:19:54.42,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,so I'm a little scared to \Nlet you stay beside Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.42,0:19:55.50,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Should I erase you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:58.05,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Don't say that like it's no big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:01.14,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Regardless, Emilia-tan's really sad
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.14,0:20:03.79,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,since her family-member-slash-pet ran off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:05.51,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,"Ran off" you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always been inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.26,0:20:10.68,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,It was good of you to call me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:13.00,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I'm glad, Subaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.41,0:20:19.03,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,Emilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.25,0:20:30.80,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Did you have another scary dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.80,0:20:31.69,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Puck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.97,0:20:39.28,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Thank goodness! Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.28,0:20:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.18,0:20:43.39,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Don't disappear like that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.27,0:20:44.93,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Puck?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:48.64,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Do I look a little smaller than usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:52.15,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I guess my limit came up \Nfaster than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:55.73,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Of course, I was consciously \Ntrying to breach our contract,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:59.36,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,so I guess it makes sense that I'd lose \Nmy greatest strengths as a spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:01.44,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Breach... our contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:03.90,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.90,0:21:06.98,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I've been by your side all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.98,0:21:09.99,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you only for \Nmy own personal reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:11.59,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,and because of your own problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:13.95,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,But from now on...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:16.06,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.24,0:21:21.92,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Eh? No, eh... W-Wait, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:28.08,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Th-This is terrible, Puck!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.08,0:21:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The stone... The stone you reside in...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.19,0:21:31.47,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Lia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.84,0:21:35.34,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I wish I could explain everything, \Nbut there's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:37.68,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,As much as it frustrates me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.68,0:21:42.56,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I'm entrusting you to the one whose \Nlove for you is second only to mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.56,0:21:44.56,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,What... are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.26,0:21:48.31,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,There's no... There's no such person...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.31,0:21:49.01,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Lia...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.49,0:21:52.55,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I'm terminating the contract \Nbetween you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.22,0:21:55.39,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I really am sorry this \Nturned out so one-sided.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.97,0:21:59.42,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Once I'm gone, the seal on \Nyour memories will be lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.42,0:22:03.18,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Remembering them will \Nprobably make you very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.64,0:22:05.90,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,You might want to cry more \Nthan you do right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.38,0:22:11.29,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}Emilia...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.84,0:22:15.02,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}I love you so, so much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.02,0:22:15.76,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.94,0:22:23.36,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,That should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.49,0:22:25.15,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,Lia...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.71,0:22:30.87,Default,Puck,0,0,0,,I {\i0}love{\i1} you more than anyone in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:48.30,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama fell unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.74,0:22:52.58,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Yeah, the spirit user's spirit left her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.98,0:22:56.26,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,If it drives her {\i1}so{\i0} nuts \Nthat she'd miss the trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.26,0:22:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then she’s of no use
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.72,0:23:00.63,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Do not say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.63,0:23:05.19,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,This is a matter of the heart, \Nso it makes me sad for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.84,0:23:08.90,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Incidentally, Young Gar, about Young Su...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.40,0:23:11.49,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,The dude who's covered in miasma?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:15.17,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,Indeed. I do know what I said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.17,0:23:18.59,Default,Ryuzu,0,0,0,,but he does not appear to have \Nany connection with the witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.21,0:23:21.67,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.39,0:23:25.32,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Get yourself to bed, you doddering old hag.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.32,0:23:28.76,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,"A rudy that stays up all night will \Nregret having short legs," ya know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.33,0:23:33.27,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.65,0:23:34.43,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.80,0:23:36.33,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I'm sure... I will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.82,0:23:40.34,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I like to believe I'll \Nbe fine by morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.74,0:23:48.48,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,A-Anyway, just don't fret over it too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.81,0:23:50.61,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,If there's anything I can do...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:53.70,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Well, I don't have much to offer, \Nbut it's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.24,0:24:01.46,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.00,0:24:03.92,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Hold my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.66,0:24:07.05,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Will you stay here until morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.53,0:24:08.55,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,If you do...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.37,0:24:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.66,0:24:13.76,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.75,0:24:15.66,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.48,0:24:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.85,0:24:23.69,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,If this is what you want, that's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.23,0:24:27.38,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Once it's morning... once \Ntomorrow comes, you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.96,0:24:29.15,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.16,0:24:32.81,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.29,0:24:43.54,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,Emilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.92,0:24:49.93,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Emilia. I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.72,0:24:54.80,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,All the people who told you that kind lie,\Nthat they wanted to protect you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.53,0:24:57.04,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,Please don't hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.01,0:25:02.52,Default,Fortuna,0,0,0,,Emilia, I love you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.29,0:25:14.11,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Mother Fortuna, you liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.28,0:25:16.82,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Puck, you liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.52,0:25:21.27,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,And Subaru... you liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.29,0:25:25.70,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.70,0:25:26.50,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,Did you find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.72,0:25:27.55,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.50,0:25:30.84,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.12,0:25:32.93,Default,Villager,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.93,0:25:34.80,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Ram, what's all the noise for?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.80,0:25:35.22,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Garf...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.09,0:25:38.33,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Do you know where Emilia-sama went?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.33,0:25:38.93,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.49,0:25:42.00,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,Emilia-sama has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.47,0:25:44.43,Default,Ram,0,0,0,,We've all split up to search for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.17,0:25:49.90,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,All right. I'll start lookin' around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.57,0:25:56.07,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Hey, Granny! You awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.80,0:26:00.05,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Someone might come by \Nlookin' for the princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:01.15,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,You better go—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.84,0:26:07.08,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Granny?! Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.50,0:26:15.46,Default - italics,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Somethin' doesn't feel right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.71,0:26:26.43,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Granny! You in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.86,0:26:29.48,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Not here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.03,0:26:40.14,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,No way. Did they...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.49,0:26:42.34,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Granny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.72,0:26:47.91,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry to disappoint you...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.08,0:26:52.31,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,But a friend asked me to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.34,0:26:57.01,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,I realize I took the short end of the stick, \Nbut I've set out to do it regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.52,0:26:59.54,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Why You...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.54,0:27:03.14,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,In truth, I had planned to talk \Nthings over with you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.14,0:27:04.77,Default,Garfiel,0,0,0,,Talk things over?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.77,0:27:07.35,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,Yes, I wanted to talk to you with Ryuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.35,0:27:11.45,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,that is, with Shima-san in attendance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.45,0:27:16.90,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,But I really wasn't expecting \Nwhat happened with Emilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.69,0:27:22.07,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,That said, all kinds of conspiratorial \Nplans were already laid out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.36,0:27:26.08,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,So now that the host of the banquet is away,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.54,0:27:28.91,Default,Otto,0,0,0,,how would you like me to play the host instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.27,0:27:35.39,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}...wanted to protect you...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.39,0:27:36.18,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm so sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.18,0:27:36.93,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please don't hate them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.93,0:27:37.49,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}Emilia...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.49,0:27:38.87,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the people who told you that kind lie...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.87,0:27:39.68,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.68,0:27:41.05,Default - flashback,Fortuna,0,0,0,,{\i1}I love you so much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.05,0:27:43.85,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Ah, Thank god, Finally found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.38,0:27:48.62,Default,Emilia,0,0,0,,Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.70,0:27:55.98,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Well, let's have a talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.97,0:27:59.07,Default,Subaru,0,0,0,,Emilia-tan.
